<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>They are INCREDIBLE, and clearly spiritual successors to Beethoven’s late quartets. Must listen — especially Nos. 2, 6, 4, 3, 1, and 5. Check out recordings by Cherubini, Van Kuijk, Gawandhaus, Henschel, Doric, and Mandelring. Don’t trust anyone who recommends Emerson or Pacifica — the tinnitus must be getting to them. That is all! <em>mic drop</em></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/urbanstrata"> /u/urbanstrata </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/132agth/felix_mendelssohns_string_quartets_dont_get/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/132agth/felix_mendelssohns_string_quartets_dont_get/">[comments]</a></span>